CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 11, 1953, pg. 6 reads: "Greeted En[i]senhower- Joy and Carolyn Waters, daughters of Mr. and Mrs. Clarence W. Waters of McKeesport, were among the thousands of youngsters and adults who attended the Easter Egg Hunt on the White House lawn in Washington, D.C. on Monday. The two youngsters not only had the opportunity to shake President Eisenhower's hand, but were given Easter eggs by the President's daughter-in-law and grandchildren.  Only three eggs were given away, and they were lucky enough to get two of them.  They are posing with their Easter eggs in above picture. - "Teenie" Harris Photo.
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Joy Waters and Carolyn Waters, holding Easter eggs, standing in interior with light colored walls
